    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fasteners used to attach washed laundry to clotheslines. There are two common types: a one-piece forked peg, and a clamp made of two pieces of wood or plastic held together with a tensioned spring, forming a pincer. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
